HEADWORD: Eductor
<hw>E*duc"tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., tutor.]</ety>
<def>One who, or that which, brings forth, elicits, or
extracts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Stimulus must be called an <qex>eductor</qex> of vital ether.</q>
<rj><qau>E. Darwin.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Edulcorant</ent>⟦br⟧
